Package: GenSEM
Title: Multilevel Multiprocess Hazard Models via Stacked Poisson Estimation
Version: 0.8.0
Authors@R: person("Carlos", "Aloisio", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "caloisio@gmail.com")
Description: Fits multilevel multiprocess systems (nonrecursive stacked-Poisson class and the recursive mixed-family class with an endogenous binary exposure) of piecewise-constant
    exponential hazard equations with correlated person-level random effects,
    following Lillard (1993) <doi:10.1016/0304-4076(93)90106-F> and the 'gsem'
    workflow of Bartus (2017) <doi:10.1177/1536867X1701700211>. Hazard
    equations are estimated as stacked Poisson regressions with log-exposure
    offsets ('glmmTMB' backend, Laplace approximation), and structural
    coefficients of nonrecursive systems are recovered from reduced-form
    estimates via the delta method (the 'nlcom' equivalent).
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: glmmTMB, numDeriv, stats
